50|$|In 2005, the Maine state {{legislature}} considered switching {{the entire state}} to Atlantic Standard Time all year long, therefore eliminating <b>Daylight</b> <b>Savings</b> <b>Time.</b> This is because in the winter, sunset can come in some areas as early as 3:42 PM. This will have no effect in the summer since DST won't be used. The bill did not pass the Maine {{state legislature}}.|$|R
25|$|Due to Australia having {{multiple}} time zones, {{especially during}} <b>Daylight</b> <b>Saving</b> <b>Time</b> (which is not kept in Queensland, Western Australia and the Northern Territory), Breakfast was not broadcast live {{in all of}} the country but was delayed in some states. In New South Wales (including ACT), Victoria and Tasmania, Breakfast was broadcast live all year round. In Queensland it was broadcast live except during <b>Daylight</b> <b>Saving</b> <b>Time</b> when it is delayed by one hour. The Northern Territory had a 30-minute delay and 90 minutes during <b>Daylight</b> <b>Saving</b> <b>Time.</b> South Australia had a 30-minute delay all year and Western Australia had a two-hour delay and three hours during <b>Daylight</b> <b>Saving</b> <b>Time.</b>|$|E
