50|$|On November 6, 2016 Pelland said he set {{his second}} unverified world record by being the first {{motorcyclist}} to document riding 28 hours in the same day. By traveling west across four time zones on the day <b>Daylight</b> <b>Savings</b> <b>Time</b> ends, Pelland rode 2000 miles and 28 hours {{all on the same}} calendar day. Pelland said he raised $6000 for MS with this ride.|$|R
